<hr />
<p>$\example{1}$ 
Express the mass of 375,000,000,000 g in: <br />
    a. Gg <br />
    b. Mg <br />
    c. Tg</p>

<p>$\solution$ <br />
$\For{a}$
\(\begin{align*}
	\text{Mass}&amp;=375,000,000,000 \un{g} \\
			&amp;= 375\x 10^9 \un{g}	&amp;&amp; \tcAal{move the decimal point 9 places to the left} \\
			&amp;= 375\un{Gg}	&amp;&amp; \tcAal{replace $10^9$ with the symbol "G"}
\end{align*}\)</p>

<p>Hence, $375,000,000,000\un{g} = 375\un{Gg}$</p>

<p>$\For{b}$
\(\begin{align*}
	\text{Mass}&amp;=375,000,000,000 \text{ g} \\
			&amp;= 375,000 \times 10^6 \text{g}	&amp;&amp; \tcAal{move the decimal point 6 places to the left} \\
			&amp;= 375,000 \text{ Mg}	&amp;&amp; \tcAal{replace $10^6$ with the symbol "M"}
\end{align*}\)</p>

<p>Hence, $375,000,000,000\un{g} = 375,000\un{Mg}$</p>

<p>$\For{c}$
\(\begin{align*}
	\text{Mass}&amp;=375,000,000,000 \text{ g} \\
			&amp;= 0.375 \times 10^{12} \text{g}	&amp;&amp; \tcAal{move the decimal point 12 places to the left} \\
			&amp;= 0.375 \text{ Tg}	&amp;&amp; \tcAal{replace $10^{12}$ with the symbol "T"}
\end{align*}\)</p>

<p>Hence, $375,000,000,000\un{g} = 0.375\un{Tg}$</p>

<hr />
<p>$\example{2}$
Express the length of 50 m in: <br />
<strong>a.</strong> km <br />
<strong>b.</strong> cm <br />
<strong>c.</strong> mm</p>

<p>$\solution$ <br />
$\For{a}$ <br />
\(\begin{align*}
	\text{Length}&amp;=50 \text{ m} \\
			&amp;= 0.05 \times 10^{3} \text{m}	&amp;&amp; \text{\tcA{move the decimal point 3 places to the left}} \\
			&amp;= 0.05 \text{ km}	&amp;&amp; \text{\tcA{replace $10^{3}$ with the symbol "k"}}
\end{align*}\)</p>

<p>Hence, 50 m = 0.05 km</p>

<p>$\For{b}$ <br />
\(\begin{align*}
	\text{Length}&amp;=50 \text{ m} \\
			&amp;= 5,000 \times 10^{-2} \text{m}	&amp;&amp; \text{\tcA{move the decimal point 2 places to the right}} \\
			&amp;= 5,000 \text{ cm}	&amp;&amp; \text{\tcA{replace $10^{-2}$ with the symbol "c"}}
\end{align*}\)</p>

<p>Hence, 50 m = 5,000 cm</p>

<p>$\For{c}$ <br />
\(\begin{align*}
	\text{Length}&amp;=50 \text{ m} \\
			&amp;= 50,000 \times 10^{-3} \text{m}	&amp;&amp; \text{\tcA{move the decimal point 3 places to the right}} \\
			&amp;= 50,000 \text{ cm}	&amp;&amp; \text{\tcA{replace $10^{-3}$ with the symbol "m"}}
\end{align*}\)</p>

<p>Hence, 50 m = 50,000 mm</p>

<p>$\example{3}$
Express the mass of $17\times 10^6$ kg in: <br />
<strong>a.</strong> dag <br />
<strong>a.</strong> Mg <br />
<strong>a.</strong> Pg</p>

<p>$\solution$
$\For{a}$ <br />
In this example, the given already has a prefix,</p>

\[\begin{align*}
	\text{Mass}&amp;=17\times 10^6 \text{ kg} \\
			&amp;= 17\times 10^6 \times 10^3 \text{ g}	&amp;&amp; \text{\tcA{replace the symbol "k" with $10^3$}} \\
			&amp;= 17\times 10^{6+3} \text{ g}&amp;&amp; \text{\tcA{multiply $10^6$ and $10^3$}} \\
			&amp;= 17\times 10^{9} \text{ g} 
\end{align*}\]

<p>Then use the same method as the previous examples,</p>

\[\begin{align*}
	\text{Mass}&amp;= 1.7\times 10^{9} \times 10^{1} \text{ g}	&amp;&amp; \text{\tcA{move the decimal point 1 place to the left}} \\
			&amp;= 1.7\times 10^{9} \text{ dag}	&amp;&amp; \text{\tcA{replace $10^{1}$ with the symbol "da"}}
\end{align*}\]

<p>Hence, $17\times 10^6$ kg = $1.7\times 10^{9}$ dag</p>

<p>$\For{b}$ <br />
We can also solve this type of example with ratios,</p>

\[\begin{align*}
	\text{Mass}&amp;=17\times 10^6 \text{ kg}
\end{align*}\]

<p>Since, k = $10^3$
\(\begin{align*}
	&amp;=17\times 10^6 \text{ \cancel{k}g} \br{\frac{10^3}{\cancel{k}}} 
		&amp;&amp; \text{\tcA{in order to cancel "k", place it at the denominator}}\\
	&amp;=17\times 10^{6+3} \text{ g}
\end{align*}\)</p>

<p>And, M = $10^6$
\(\begin{align*}
	&amp;=17\times 10^9 \text{ g} \br{\frac{M}{10^6}} \\
	&amp;=17\times 10^{9-6} \text{ Mg} \\
	&amp;=17\times 10^3 \text{ Mg}
\end{align*}\)</p>

<p>Hence, $17\times 10^6$ kg = $17\times 10^3$ Mg</p>

<p>$\For{c}$ <br />
\(\begin{align*}
	\phantom{a} \text{Mass}&amp;=17\times 10^6 \text{ kg} &amp;\\
			&amp;=17\times 10^6 \text{ \cancel{k}g} \br{\frac{10^3}{\cancel{k}}}  
				\br{ \frac{P}{10^{15}} } \\
			&amp;= 17\times 10^{6+3-15} \text{ Pg} \\
			&amp;= 17\times 10^{-6} \text{ Pg}
\end{align*}\)</p>

